Sol, the Lionheart - Wizard

Alchemist/Brewmaster
	Alchemy & Brewing don't exist as Wizard subclasses, is DM okay with homebrewing something?

Either Triton or Human, can it be human variant? Down to DM
	Age. Late 20s
	Size. Medium, tall and built out (not a classic wizard)
	Speed. 30ft
	Languages. Common + 1 (DM?)

Questions:
	Class - Can we be Triton or could I be a variant human (Innistrad)?
		Triton
			Ability Score Increase. One by 2 and another by 1  OR  Three by 1
			Amphibious. You can breathe air and water.
			Control Air and Water. - 1st Fog Cloud, 3rd Gust of Wind, 5th Water Walk
			Darkvision
			Emissary of the Sea - Communicate simple ideas to any Beast, Elemental, or Monstrosity that has a swimming speed.
			Guardian of the Depths - Resistance to cold damage.

		Innistrad - Nephalia 
			Ability Score Increase. Your Intelligence and Charisma scores each increase by 1.
			Breadth of Knowledge. You gain proficiency in any combination of four skills or with four tools of your choice.

	Water breathing importance?
		Water breathing cantrip (HB?)
		Potion of Water Breathing ability to make?
		Or level 3 spell "Water Breathing"

	What is the advantage of brewing a spell into a potion?
	  More uses, save across days, longer lasting, more potent?
	  10 mins to brew?

	Drinking a potion officially is an action, will we run it as action or bonus action?

Proficiencies
	Armor: None
	Weapons: Daggers, darts, slings, quarterstaffs, light crossbows
	Tools: None
	Saving Throws: Intelligence, Wisdom
	Skills: Choose two from Arcana, History, Insight, Investigation, Medicine, and Religion

The Spell Book:
	A server's book - small notebook that waitors/waitresses use

Personality:
	Full of pride and his confidence rarely falters
	Consumes copious amount of alcohol and other alchemical drinks
	Takes an inhuman amount to get him drunk
	Always sipping at various experimental drinks and potions (flavour not of any use)
	He is very comfortable trading in markets and travelling the seas

Background:
	Comes from a large trading port and has lived on or around boats for most of his life.
	He noticed the giant lack of good scran on ships and found a massive gap in the market serving incredible food and booze to sailors and pirates as they travelled.
	As he travelled he also begins experimenting with not just boozes but alchemical potions with arcane spells.

Wizard
	Spell slots regained fully on long rest
	Spell slots regained 1/day on short rest half wiz level rounded up

Levelling (Wizard)
	Each time you gain a wizard level, add 2x wizard spells of your choice to your spellbook. Each of these spells must be of a level for which you have spell slots.

	1: Spellcasting, 3x cantrips, Spell book - 6x 1st level spells.
	2: Arcane tradition (ALCHEMIST/BREWMASTER)
	3: 1/long rest can swap a cantrip with another, 2nd level spells
	4: ASI/Feat
	5: 3rd Level Spells, PB increase
	6: Arcane tradition (ALCHEMIST/BREWMASTER)
	7: 4th Level Spells
	8: ASI/Feat
	9: 5th Level Spells, PB increase
	10: Arcane tradition (ALCHEMIST/BREWMASTER)

On your adventures, you might find other spells that you can add to your spellbook.
	For each level of the spell, the process takes 2 hours and costs 50 gp.

